From 419440fcf90deec95c7a29a93d8b0a3b6f18d8f6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: t <t@t.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 22:04:19 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add on-screen NFC debug log + close/reopen-per-read RF
 strategy
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

We keep going in circles guessing what the WizarPOS does. This patch makes
the device tell us:

Native (ValidatorHardwarePlugin.kt):
- Rolling timestamped trace buffer (rfTrace) + trace() logging every native
  RF step: recycle/close, open(), waitForCardPresent, resultCode, getCard,
  member searchEnd, exceptions (with real targetException unwrapped).
- readNfcOnce now numbers each read (read#1, read#2, …) and does a FULL
  close()+reopen() before every read (most robust reset for the native
  singleton), tracing each sub-step so we can see exactly where read#2 fails.
- New channel methods: nfcTrace (dump the log), nfcMethods (list which
  native RF methods actually exist on this SDK build: open/close/
  waitForCardPresent/waitForCardAbsent/cancelRequest/searchEnd/detach/…).

Flutter (validator_screen.dart / validator_hardware.dart):
- Tap the on-screen 'NFC: … · atinge pentru LOG' line to open a live,
  auto-refreshing debug panel: shows method availability + the full step
  trace, a 'Test read' button (tap a card, watch read#1/#2/#3 grow) and a
  'Copy' button to copy the whole log to clipboard.
- Loop pauses while the panel is open so manual test reads don't interleave.

flutter analyze clean; APK 37.8MB (arm64).
